Hi - 
So what did you think was thought-provoking about the movie?
I thought the inclusivity message in Zootopia was the most thought-provoking aspect of the film.  What about you?
Yeah I thought it was really cool how they were always trying to look past the stereotypes and not use hurtful assumptions - I think my wife and I liked the movie more than the kids did
Yeah I agree.  Sometimes the message is too deep for children to understand, so it makes for a good experience for both parents and children alike.  Do you watch a lot of family comedies?
Yeah we watch a lot of family stuff - usually prefer a combo of funny, smart, and thought-provoking
I liked the scene where she is hustled by the con artist fox duo.  What was your favorite scene?
I thought it was comical that even though she was valedictorian of the academy, the chief gave her parking duty just because he thought she was a timid rabbit

Yeah that was a great scene.  Do you agree with the average rating for the movie 
on Rotten Tomatoes being an 8/10?  Do you think it should be higher?
Sorry having a little tech difficulties with it loading up
Yeah I was just looking at that. I think its pretty awesome that they gave ti a 98%
98% is much higher than I though it should be.  I think the 8/10 that both Rotten Tomatoes and IMDB have is just about right.
Do you think the blackmailing that happens in the movie is a little too advanced for children?
